reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Long wear mascara
reviews.reviewText: This mascara really added a lot of volume to my lashes. I only had to use two coats to see a dramatic difference. It barely flaked on my lower lashes after wearing it all day. It's easy to remove without tugging. This is my new go to mascara. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this mascara!
reviews.reviewText: Wife - I read the reviews for this mascara and decided to try it. It will be my main mascara now! It makes my lashes fuller and longer...the best part is that it doesn't flake or smudge!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is my second favorite mascara (sky high first) I have to use water proof and this comes off relatively easy with micellar water. Doesn’t leave much on your face after a days worth of wearing and curls the lashes so good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is comparable to benefits roller lash for me but much more affordable. I might still dip roller lash brush in L’Oréal to get more curl. Min flaking. Washes off easy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars How I made it work
reviews.reviewText: I had high hopes for this mascara. My current favorite is another L’Oréal mascara. This doesn’t volumize my lashes at all. They get longer but no volume. Additionally this smudges horrendously. If you have even the tiniest bit of wateriness in your eyes, this mascara will end up everywhere. It smudged even when my eyes weren’t watery. The formula is very wet even after two weeks of owning this. The best thing about this mascara is that the wand is a good size for smaller eyes. I did like the length, but the smudging was a deal breaker for me.Update: I was determined to make this mascara work because I paid good money for it, and I don't like to waste things. So, I've been using it at a layering mascara, and I have had zero issues with smudging as long as I put another mascara over it. This mascara gives me super long lashes, so I put this one on for length, and then I layer Lash Paradise over it. Works like a charm! I don't know if I'll repurchase though, but I'm making it work for now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My new favorite
reviews.reviewText: TBH, I didn't have high hopes but I was so sick of paying high dollar for brands like Urban Decay, Bare Minerals, etc. I was shocked at how beautiful this particular product works. Price is good and it's not dried out, goes on easily, and makes me look like I have eyelashes. I hope they don't change this at all. Love the brush design too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Buy! Great Results!
reviews.reviewText: I get so many compliments when I wear this mascara! Easily removable, I just use a mascara primer before I apply and remove it with cetaphil gentle skin cleanser at night.

I have been using Loreal Mascara all of my adult life and the Voluminous family was the one I used. I tried the Panoramic and I can say this stuff is amazing and it's my new mascara, no going back, no changes. Volume and length extraordinaire!
The best mascara I have ever had!!!

I've been searching for a replacement mascara for a couple of years since the one I loved was discontinued. I was very eager to try this L’Oréal Panorama product.Overall, I liked (but didn't "love") this mascara, and I will definitely continue to use it until I run out. It is a very deep black, and I like how bold the colour is on my lashes. It does a good job of lengthening, which is what I'm after--the brush seems to be a firm silicone, and not curved, and I found it very easy to work with for both upper and lower lashes.It goes on quite wet, and that gives me a little time to comb and separate lashes before it dries. I don't find it too clumpy, but I do find I like a little more separation than the brush offers.Once dry, I like that this mascara does not smudge. It also washes off fairly easily.The only thing I'm not thrilled about is that it starts to flake off my lashes fairly soon after drying. This is a problem I have with a LOT of mascaras (even though I am very careful to dry my lashes thoroughly before applying mascara). I know it's possible to find mascaras that don't flake off my lashes, but this is not one of them. I will give this Panorama mascara kudos for minimal flaking (it's not huge chunks, and not as much as I've experienced with other products), but I will keep looking for a product that doesn't have this effect on my lashes.Overall, this is a good mascara, it looks good, doesn't smudge and gives me nice length.
